news.title: HC questions embargo on repair works in affluent unauthorised colonies like Sainik Farms
news.para: ​The court noted that some of the structures need urgent repairs and may collapse anytime and said there should be some mechanism that may determine if any property is so precariously placed that may fall.

news.title: Maintain status quo on buildings near Goa airport:SC
news.para: The SC sought a reply from the respondents, and granted permission to the 45 petitioners to file a SLP before it, in the matter.

news.title: Bihar government not to permit new brick kilns: Minister
news.para: The number of brick kilns would be controlled and the minimum distance prescribed between two brick kilns would also be adhered to strictly. All the brick kilns which have not so far adopted new manufacturing technology would be closed, he said.

news.title: Pune cantonment board to scrutinise dilapidated buildings
news.para: Subrat Pal, chief executive officer (CEO) of the PCB, told TOI on Tuesday, “Our officials will conduct the survey and identify dangerous structures within our limits.

news.title: Coimbatore corporation's panel approves property tax hike
news.para: The council on April 11 passed a resolution increasing the property tax for residential, commercial and industrial buildings as per the state government’s order.

news.title: Nagpur civic body delaying action against 768 illegal buildings?
news.para: Nagpur city has around 1,544 buildings that have violated sanctioned plans and indulged in illegal constructions. However, NMC acted only against 300 structures, revealed data obtained from its enforcement department.

news.title: Hand over upkeep charge to RWA, say Orris Aster Court residents
news.para: The residents have been demanding the handover of the maintenance to the RWA of the society for the last one year alleging pathetic services anclaimed that the developer is imposing arbitrary charges.

news.title: Chandigarh: Fourteenth cheating FIR against GBP group
news.para: ​​The complainants filed the complaints at the SSP public window in Sector 9. After verifying the facts, police registered one more cheating FIR against the directors of GBP group.

news.title: Kochi: Panel meet on Maradu flats razing on May 23
news.para: Authorities of institutions, builders, promoters and others concerned with the construction of the illegal flats which were later razed to the ground, have been asked to appear before the committee in Ernakulam.

news.title: Bhumika group raises Rs 100 crore, in talks to raise more for Udaipur mall
news.para: The company is in talks to raise another Rs 200 crore debt to fund the construction of phase 2 of its 3.5 lakh sq. ft. retail space in Udaipur mall. Majority or phase 1 has already been leased out.

news.title: SC to consider hearing SFIO's plea against Delhi HC relief to Sahara group firms
news.para: ​A bench comprising Chief Justice N V Ramana and Justice Hima Kohli was told by Solicitor General Tushar Mehta that there was some apprehension on the part of the petitioner (SFIO) with regard to another bench recently staying a look out circular against Sahara Group chief Subrata Roy.

news.title: Mumbai: Builder to pay Rs 37 lakh for delay in giving flat possession
news.para: The commission passed similar orders in complaints filed by 13 such flat buyers. They had purchased the 690 square feet Bandra East flats for Rs 1.96 crore in 2011.

news.title: Maharashtra govt issues special measures for Navi Mumbai housing revival program
news.para: As part of this program, the Minister of Urban Development Eknath Shinde has announced the government will issue Occupancy Certificates (OC) to eligible projects out of the 94 stuck projects within a month of them receiving clearance from the Maharashtra Coastal Zone Management Authority (MCZMA).

news.title: Ansal Esencia residents want Gurugram civic body to take charge of township
news.para: Spread across 250 acres, the project was launched in 2011. Possession started in 2014. Residents pointed out that despite paying internal and external development charges to the developer along with property tax to the government, they are being deprived of basic amenities.

news.title: Noida authority not financial creditor but operational creditor: SC
news.para: ​The apex court delivered its verdict on appeals filed by NOIDA in which a common question arose as to whether the authority is entitled to be treated as a financial creditor within the meaning of the IBC.
